get.summary: Retrieve data about specified customer and their related accounts

externalDocs.description: Learn more about user operations provided by this API.

get.description:
This method is used to retrieve information for the specified customer's related accounts.  Name and address information and general demographic information for the customer is also returned.

On the Deposit System, there may be multiple time deposits under one account number, each identified by a time deposit ID.   If there are multiple time deposits under an account, the account level balance fields will reflect a roll-up of the balances in the individual time deposits.

On the Loan System, there may be multiple notes (loans) under one account number, each identified by a note number.  There are no account level balance fields that reflect a roll-up of the balances in the individual notes.

prevYtdLedgr.description: Average ledger balance for the previous year.

defrdIncomInd.description: Deferred income indicator. Yes or No.

depCat.description: Code indicating the account's deposit category.

depCatDesc.description: Description of the account's deposit category.

currBal.description: Current balance. Account's ledger balance plus or minus today's on-line activity.

acctAvailBal.description: Amount of the account balance that is available for withdrawal.  This amount reflects holds, float, on-line activity, and, if applicable, unused PRA, overdraft limits, unavailable funds limit, penalty, and withholding.  This field only appears for individual customers.

availBalMultiTierInd.description: Multi-tier indicator.  If this indicator is set to Yes, the Available Balance field will be zeroed out.

collBal.description: Collected balance.  Ledger balance minus collectable float.  This field only appears for organizational customers.

ytdCollBal.description: Average collected balance since the beginning of the current year.

prevYtdCollBal.description: Average collected balance for the previous year.

ytdLedgBal.description: Average ledger balance since the beginning of the current year.

prevYtdLedgBal.description: Average ledger balance for the previous year.

certCurrBal.description: Certificate current balance. Ledger balance plus or minus today's on-line activity.

odsYtd.description: Number of overdrafts since the beginning of the current year.

odsPrev.description: Number of overdrafts since the beginning of the current year.

returnsYtd.description: Number of items returned since the beginning of the current year.

returnsPrev.description: Number of items returned for the previous year.

custTyp.description: Indicates the type of customer.  I - Individual  O - Organization

taxCde.description: Code identifying the type of taxpayer identification number.  F - Federal taxpayer identification number.  N - No taxpayer identification number.  S - Social security number.  T - Individual taxpayer identification number.

custStatus.description: Indicates the status of the customer record.  C - Closed.  D - Delete.  I - Inactive.  O - Open.  R - Reopen.

primOffcr.description: Number of the primary officer assigned to the customer, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

secndryOffcr.description: Number of the secondary officer assigned to the customer, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

custSinceDte.description: Date the customer started a relationship with the bank.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

custOpenDte.description: Date the customer record was established on the system.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

custClsDte.description: Date the customer record was closed.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

brnch.description: Branch number.   Identifies the branch where the customer record resides.

amtPstDue.description: Amount past due at last statement date.

statmntBal.description: Balance as of the last statement date.

amtOverLmt.description: Amount over limit at last statement date.

balance1.description: Balance 1 from a miscellaneous application interface.  CCM - Current balance.  CMS - Market value.  INVMT - Product balance.  MLOAN - Current balance.  TRST - Market value.  CDARS - Book balance.

balance2.description: Balance 2 from a miscellaneous application interface.  CCM - Payment amount.  CMS - Market value.  INVMT - Not applicable.  MLOAN - Original balance.  TRST - Net cash amount.  CDARS - Current payout - anticipated payout today.

balance3.description: Balance 3 from a miscellaneous application interface.

balance4.description: Balance 4 from a miscellaneous application interface.

currProfScore.description: The current month's profitability results for the customer.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by C.

ytdProfScore.description: The average year-to-date profitability results for the customer.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by Y.

r12ProfScore.description: The average profitability results for the customer over the last 12 months.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by R.

lstMaintUser.description: The user ID that last performed maintenance on the customer.

lstMaintDte.description: The date maintenance was last performed on the customer. Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

acctTyp.description: Identifies a set of account characteristics, as defined on Bank Control Account Option Segment 405.

purpose.description: Indicates the type of account and corresponds to the credit bureau field, Association Code, for credit bureau reporting purposes.  B - Business.  J - Joint (personal).  S - Single (personal).  1-9 - Personal (user-defined).

commtmntInd.description: Indicates whether this account has any related commitments.  Yes or No.

riskRatng.description: User-defined risk rating for the account.

orgTyp1.description: Code that identifies accounts owned by special groups of customers.

orgTyp2.description: Code that identifies accounts owned by special groups of customers.

e1E2.description: Code indicating whether customer is primary or secondary owner of this account.  901 - Primary.  902 - Secondary.

e1E2Desc.description: Description of code indicating whether customer is primary or secondary owner of this account.

e2E1.description: Code indicating customer's relationship to account, as defined on Relationship Codes Segment 605 of Bank Control.

e2E1Desc.description: Description of customer's relationship to account, as defined on Relationship Codes Segment 605 of Bank Control.

relaTyp.description: Code indicating the type of relationship.  CA - Customer-to-account.

effDte.description: Effective date of the customer-to-account relationship.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

expDte.description: Expiration date of the customer-to-account relationship.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

ownerInd.description: This field is used to determine whether or not the account is owned.   If this field is set to N, then the account will be excluded from the results.

negFileRsnCde.description: Code identifying why card is placed on negative file.  The following values are defined by FIS. Your institution can choose to use other values.  A - Address correction.  B - Closed by institution.  C - Closed by customer.  F - Fraud.  G - Empty envelope.  I - Invalid account.  K - Kiting.  L - Lost.  N - No activity.  O - Overdraft.  S - Stolen.  W - Warm status.  Y - Compromised.

loanCat.description: Loan category.  Broad classification for identifying loans with similar processing characteristics.  C - Commercial.  F - Floor plan.  G - General accounts receivable.  I - Installment.  M - Mortgage.  P - Purchased loan.  R - Revolving credit.  S - Specific accounts receivable.

status.description: Indicates whether the loan is partially or completely charged off, and whether the loan is earning interest. May also identify the reason for nonaccrual or charge-off status. See Loans Reference Manual for a complete list of status codes.

origBal.description: Original principal balance of the note.

acctTotBankShare.description: Bank's share of all outstanding loans associated with the account.

issueDte.description: Date the note was issued.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

maturtyDte.description: Date the note will mature.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

rateOvr.description: Rate of interest paid on the note. For split-rate notes, the rate on any balance over the split-rate limit. For variable-rate notes, the current rate.

rateUndr.description: For split-rate notes, the rate on any balances up through the split-rate limit.

timesLate15.description: Number of times the note was 15 to 29 days past due.

timesLate30.description: Number of times the note was 30 to 59 days past due.

timesLate60.description: Number of times the note was 60 to 89 days past due.

timesLate90.description: Number of times the note was 90 or more days past due.

paidInd.description: Indicates the paid status of the loan.  0 - Not paid off.  C - Paid off, appears on the Credit Bureau Paid Out report (R-7201).  M - Not paid off, appears on the Miscellaneous Balances report (R-6228).  P - Paid off.  T - Transferred.  Z - Principal paid but interest due (Bill Type F only).

type.description: PRA/LOC type.  Represents a set of processing options and defaults for overdraft protection on a revolving credit plan attached to a checking account, as defined on PRA/Line of Credit Segment 245 of Bank Control.

availLine.description: Maximum authorized credit amount that can be borrowed.

amtDue.description: Total amount of PRA payments due including past and current amounts due.

acctStatus.description: Indicates the status of the account.

openDte.description: Date the account was opened.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

closeDte.description: Date the account was closed.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

brnch.description: Branch number.  Identifies the branch where the account record resides.

costCntr.description: Identifies the responsible cost center for the account.

primOffcr.description: Number of the primary officer assigned to the account, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

secndryOffcr.description: Number of the secondary officer assigned to the account, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

commitAvailBal.description: Total available balances of all commitments associated with the account.

commitsUsed.description: Total used balances of all commitments associated with the account.

guaranteed.description: Indicates whether an account is endorsed or guaranteed.  Yes or No.

acctTotBankShareTot.description: Bank's share of all outstanding loans associated with the account.

currBalTot.description: Total of principal balances of all notes.

origBalTot.description: Total of original principal balances of all notes.

busTyp.description: Describes the customer's type of business, as specified on Demographic Description Segment 615 of Bank Control.

busSinceDte.description: Date the customer began the business.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

brthDte.description: Customer's date of birth.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

householdStatus.description: Indicates the status of the household record.  C - Closed.  D - Delete.  I - Inactive.  O - Open.  R - Reopen.

brnch.description: Branch number.   Identifies the branch where the household record resides.

costCntr.description: Identifies the responsible cost center for the household.

primOffcr.description: Number of the primary officer assigned to the household, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

secndryOffcr.description: Number of the secondary officer assigned to the household, as specified on Officer Segment 110 of Bank Control.

householdSinceDte.description: Date the household started a relationship with the bank.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

householdOpenDte.description: Date the household record was established on the system.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

householdCloseDte.description: Date the household record was closed.  Format: CCYY-MM-DD.

currProfScore.description: The current month's profitability results for the household.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by C.

ytdProfScore.description: The average year-to-date profitability results for the household.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by Y.

r12ProfScore.description: The average profitability results for the household over the last 12 months.  Values are 1 through 10, followed by R.

morePages.description: Indicates if more data exists to be returned - always returned

nextPageCursor.description: If there is more data to be returned, resubmit the call using the value returned here to retrieve the next set of data.  Must leave this field blank for the first call to the API.

bnkNum.description: Bank number of the customer record.

applnCode.description: Customer code of the customer record.

applnNum.description: Customer number of the customer record.

recordTypeGender.description: The record type of the customer.

forceHouseHoldInd.description: Indicate if customer is in a forced household relation.

prospectInd.description: Indicates if the record is a prospect customer.

country.description: Country - 3 character ISO country code, if present.

branch.description: Branch where customer record was opened.

remarksInd.description: Customer remarks indicator - indicates if customer record has remarks.

addressLastChange.description: Date household address was last changed.

addressReferenceNum.description: Address reference number of the store household address.

delimiter.description: Indicates the next set of relationship data for a single related customer, account or sub account no value.

relBankNum.description: Bank number of the related account.

relAppCode.description: Application code of the related account.

relAppNum.description: Application number of the related account.

e1ToE2Ind.description: Code value of the relationship between the account and customer.

e2ToE1Ind.description: Code value of the relationship between the customer and account.

depBankNum.description: The bank number of this account.

depAccNum.description: The account number of this account.

depOpenInd.description: Indicates the status of the account.

depEmpInd.description: Indicates if the account holder is an employee of the organization.

depCategory.description: The deposit category of this account.
